data.value: The capital is a Buddhist temple in the Asakusa district of Tokyo. It is known as one of the oldest and most important temples in Tokyo. Senso-ji, belonging to the Tendai sect of Buddhism, became an independent temple after World War II. This temple is dedicated to bodhisattva Kannon and is now the eternal resting place for important actors like Utaemon Ichikawa, Ichikawa Danj ,rō IX, Yoarashi Okinu and Ichikawa Danjuro VIII. Opened in 645, Senso-ji is one of Japan's attractions.
